<@section "Tips" "cuenta">
<p>
<ol>
<li>
If you are already a diver, don’t forget to bring your basic equipment, dive light, and binnacle. The wetsuit is optional.
</li><li>
Moreover, don’t forget to bring solar protector, repellent, comfortable clothes, and a pair of shoes with non-skid soles to have comfortable ecologic trips.
</li><li>
Remember that there aren’t banks in Capurganá or cash machines, and then you should bring cash.
</li><li>
When getting here, enjoy the environment without pollution; breathe deep and give to your lungs a fresh air. Here there aren’t cars and the most common transport are the bicycle, the carthorses for cargo transport, and the boats to go from a seaside town to other.
</li><li>
When choosing Capurganá as your next holydays destine, don’t think you are in those traditional diving centers where the hotel is the only opportunity to have fun after diving. Here you will find a lot of fun outside: have a walk around, talk to local people and try the Capurganá’s food. 
</li>
</ol>
</p>
